{
  "texts": [
    "Columns (4) through (6) present similar analyses for Rust versus Haskell packages, with coefficients translating to an increase of 37.46%, 33.66% and 32.03% in releases at a mean value of 0.182 release per quarter.",
    "Appendix Figure A4 visualizes the Synthetic DiD results.",
    "First, we estimate models using the log-transformed dependent variable to address the skewed distribution.",
    "The results for two methods of categorizing innovation types-function addition and LLM categorizationare presented in Appendix Tables A8 and A9, respectively.",
    "In function creation analysis (Appendix Table A8), commits with a new function definition increase by 0.186, which translates to 20.43% ((e 0.186 -1) * 100 = 20.43%), whereas commits without a new function definition increase by 0.397, which translates to 48.73%."
